(5. Independent Study Guidance) Tj
T*
(For independent study, the learner should revisit the explanation and then practise with) Tj
T*
(tasks that reflect distance-time and velocity reasoning. The most effective habit is to) Tj
T*
(read the worked example slowly, restate each step in simple words, and then attempt a) Tj
T*
(similar question alone. This turns Motion into something the student can genuinely study) Tj
T*
(and understand without depending completely on a teacher.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Key Ideas To Remember) Tj
T*
(- Motion should first be understood as a scientific principle before it is treated as an) Tj
T*
(exam topic.) Tj
T*
(- The learner must understand distance, displacement, speed, and velocity because it) Tj
T*
(controls how questions in Motion are answered correctly.) Tj
T*
(- A strong answer in Motion uses the correct physical reasoning process and explains why) Tj
T*
(that method fits the task.) Tj
T*
(- Comparing two journeys using distance and displacement is the type of application that) Tj
T*
(helps move the topic from explanation to mastery.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Step-By-Step Method) Tj
T*
(1. Read the question or example and identify the part connected to Motion.) Tj
T*
(2. Recall the specific rule, process, or principle behind distance, displacement, speed,) Tj
T*
(and velocity.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct physical reasoning process step by step instead of jumping to the) Tj
T*
(answer.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the result carefully and confirm that it matches the requirement of the topic.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Examples) Tj
T*
(Worked Example 1) Tj
T*
(1. Start with an example based on comparing two journeys using distance and) Tj
T*
(displacement.) Tj
T*
(2. Identify the exact idea in distance, displacement, speed, and velocity that the) Tj
T*
(question is testing.) Tj
T*
(3. Apply the correct method for Motion step by step without skipping reasoning.) Tj
T*
(4. Check the final answer and explain why it is correct.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Worked Example 2) Tj
T*
(1. Choose a second example that still focuses on distance-time and velocity reasoning.) Tj
T*
(2. Break the task into smaller parts and link each part to the rule being used.) Tj
T*
(3. Point out how to avoid treating speed and velocity as the same quantity while solving) Tj
T*
(it.) Tj
T*
(4. Review the result and connect it back to the topic overview.) Tj
T*
